add.push(
  {id:"fd-rn-screens",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"RN + Expo Screen Pack",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4F1}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Создай RN + Expo screen pack (auth / home / detail).\n\nSETUP:\n- npx create-expo-app --template.\n- React Navigation 7: native stack + bottom tabs.\n- TypeScript strict.\n- Zustand / Jotai для state.\n- TanStack Query для async.\n\nSCREENS:\n1. Login: email + password, social buttons, forgot.\n2. Register: email + password + confirm.\n3. Home: list с pull-to-refresh + infinite scroll (FlashList).\n4. Detail: params route, image header, actions.\n5. Profile: avatar, settings, logout.\n\nNAV:\nAuthStack (Login, Register) → MainTabs (Home, Profile) — conditional on auth.\n\nSHARED:\n- useTheme (light/dark).\n- ErrorBoundary.\n- OfflineBanner (NetInfo).\n- SafeAreaProvider.\n\nA11Y:\n- accessibilityLabel на всё интерактивное.\n- Minimum tap target 44×44.\n- Dynamic font scaling (allowFontScaling).',
   tags:["mobile","react-native","expo","navigation","screens"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"RN screens",related:["fd-push-notif","fd-offline-first"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-flutter-widgets",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Flutter Widget Library",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4A0}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Создай Flutter widget library bootstrap.\n\nSTRUCTURE:\nlib/\n  theme/ (colors, text_styles, spacing).\n  widgets/ (atoms: Button, Input; molecules: Card, FormField; organisms: Header, ListItem).\n  screens/\n  models/\n  services/\n\nSTATE:\n- Riverpod / Bloc / Provider.\n- Для small — Provider.\n- Для complex — Riverpod.\n\nNAV:\n- go_router (declarative).\n- Deep linking.\n- Auth guard redirect.\n\nTHEMING:\n- ThemeData.light / dark.\n- ColorScheme.fromSeed.\n- Custom text theme с Google Fonts.\n\nWIDGETS:\n- Stateless где возможно.\n- Const constructors.\n- Keys для stateful lists.\n- ListView.builder для длинных списков.\n\nTESTING:\n- widget_test: pumpWidget + find + tap.\n- integration_test для e2e.\n- Golden tests для visual regression.',
   tags:["mobile","flutter","dart","widgets","riverpod"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Flutter library",related:["fd-rn-screens"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-ios-swiftui",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"iOS SwiftUI Screen",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F34F}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Создай iOS SwiftUI screen + navigation.\n\nPROJECT:\n- Xcode 16, iOS 17+ target.\n- App lifecycle: @main App struct.\n- NavigationStack (iOS 16+).\n\nPATTERNS:\n- MVVM: View + ViewModel (ObservableObject).\n- @StateObject vs @ObservedObject.\n- @Environment для shared state.\n\nSCREENS:\n- List с NavigationLink → Detail.\n- Form с @State + Binding.\n- TabView main nav.\n- Sheet / fullScreenCover modals.\n\nNETWORK:\n- async/await URLSession.\n- Codable for JSON.\n- Task { } в .task modifier (cancel on disappear).\n\nPERSISTENCE:\n- SwiftData (iOS 17+).\n- UserDefaults для settings.\n- Keychain для secrets.\n\nA11Y:\n- .accessibilityLabel / .accessibilityHint.\n- Dynamic Type support.\n- VoiceOver test.',
   tags:["mobile","ios","swiftui","swift","navigation"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"SwiftUI app",related:["fd-android-compose","fd-rn-screens"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-android-compose",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Android Jetpack Compose",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F916}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Создай Android Jetpack Compose screen.\n\nSETUP:\n- Kotlin + Compose BOM.\n- Material 3.\n- Navigation Compose.\n- Hilt для DI.\n\nPATTERNS:\n- MVI / MVVM + StateFlow.\n- @Composable functions.\n- remember / rememberSaveable.\n- LaunchedEffect для side effects.\n\nSCREENS:\nNavHost → composable("home") { HomeScreen() }.\nArguments: composable("detail/{id}") { backStackEntry → ... }.\n\nSTATE:\n- UiState sealed class (Loading, Success, Error).\n- ViewModel exposes StateFlow<UiState>.\n- collectAsStateWithLifecycle в Composable.\n\nLAZY LIST:\n- LazyColumn + items().\n- key = { it.id } для стабильности.\n\nTHEMING:\n- ColorScheme.lightColorScheme / darkColorScheme.\n- Typography + Shapes.\n- Dynamic color (Android 12+).\n\nA11Y:\n- Modifier.semantics { contentDescription = "..." }.\n- 48dp minimum touch target.',
   tags:["mobile","android","compose","kotlin","jetpack"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Compose app",related:["fd-ios-swiftui"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-push-notif",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Push Notifications",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F514}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2h",
   text:'Реализуй push notifications (APNS / FCM / Expo).\n\nARCHITECTURE:\n1. Device registers → получает push token.\n2. Backend: сохранить token + user_id.\n3. Send: POST to FCM / APNS / Expo Push API.\n4. Platform routing: iOS → APNS, Android → FCM.\n\nEXPO:\n- expo-notifications.\n- getExpoPushTokenAsync.\n- Expo Push API: https://exp.host/--/api/v2/push/send.\n\nNATIVE:\n- iOS: UNUserNotificationCenter + APNS certs/keys.\n- Android: FirebaseMessagingService + FCM.\n\nPAYLOAD:\n{to: token, title, body, data: {type, id}, sound, badge, priority: "high"}.\n\nDEEP LINK:\n- Tap notification → open specific screen.\n- Handle background / foreground / killed state.\n\nPREFERENCES:\n- Per-user channels (transactional, marketing, updates).\n- Opt-out UI в settings.\n- Quiet hours.\n\nQUOTA:\n- APNS rate limits.\n- Batch send для massive campaigns.',
   tags:["mobile","push-notifications","fcm","apns","expo"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Push setup",related:["fd-rn-screens"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-offline-first",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Offline-First Sync",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4F6}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~3-4h",
   text:'Offline-first sync strategy.\n\nLOCAL DB:\n- SQLite (WatermelonDB / RxDB / Drift).\n- Realm.\n- PowerSync / ElectricSQL (с built-in sync).\n\nSYNC:\n- Pull: fetch changes since last_sync.\n- Push: queue локальных mutations.\n- Retry с backoff при network error.\n\nCONFLICTS:\n- Last-write-wins (simple).\n- CRDT (сложнее, но merge без conflict).\n- Server-authoritative + client override.\n\nOPTIMISTIC UI:\n- UI обновляется сразу на local write.\n- Background sync publishes changes.\n- Rollback + notify при reject от server.\n\nQUEUE:\n- Persistent queue (SQLite).\n- Ordered mutations.\n- Idempotency key.\n\nCONNECTIVITY:\n- @react-native-community/netinfo.\n- Sync при regained connectivity.\n- Background fetch (iOS) / WorkManager (Android).\n\nUI:\n- Offline banner.\n- Sync indicator / last-synced time.\n- Pending changes badge.',
   tags:["mobile","offline","sync","sqlite","crdt"],difficulty:"advanced",output:"Offline sync",related:["fd-rn-screens","fd-push-notif"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"rl-mobile-cicd",m:"/ralph-loop",mk:"claude",role:"Mobile CI/CD (Fastlane/EAS)",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F6E0}",ac:"#61dafb",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'/ralph-loop "' + E + 'ЗАДАЧА: Mobile CI/CD (Fastlane / EAS Build).\n\nEAS (Expo):\n- eas build --platform all --profile production.\n- Credentials управляются EAS.\n- OTA updates: eas update.\n- Submit: eas submit --platform ios.\n\nFASTLANE (native):\n- Fastfile lanes: beta, release.\n- match для signing certs (encrypted git repo).\n- scan: запуск тестов.\n- gym: build iOS.\n- pilot: TestFlight upload.\n- supply: Play Store upload.\n\nPIPELINE:\n1. Lint + type-check.\n2. Unit + snapshot tests.\n3. Build (production).\n4. Upload artifact.\n5. Deploy в internal testing track.\n6. Manual promote → TestFlight → App Store.\n\nSTORE CONFIG:\n- Screenshots (5.5", 6.5", iPad).\n- App privacy (iOS).\n- Data safety form (Android).\n- Content rating.\n- What\'s new — из changelog.' + A + '" --completion-promise "DONE"',
   tags:["mobile","ci-cd","fastlane","eas","deployment"],difficulty:"advanced",output:"Mobile CI/CD",related:["fd-rn-screens"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
);

// ── Code quality (6) ──
add.push(
  {id:"sm-dead-code",m:"/simplify",mk:"claude",role:"Dead Code Elimination",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F9F9}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~1h",
   text:'Проведи dead code elimination.\n\nTOOLS:\n- knip / ts-prune (TS): unused exports.\n- depcheck (JS): unused deps.\n- vulture / dead (Python): unused code.\n- cargo-machete (Rust).\n- Unreferenced files: find src/ | xargs grep.\n\nCATEGORIES:\n1. Unused imports.\n2. Unused variables / functions.\n3. Unused exports.\n4. Dead branches (unreachable).\n5. Unused packages в package.json.\n6. Commented-out блоки кода.\n7. Old feature flags (всегда true/false).\n8. Deprecated API endpoints без callers.\n9. Unused translations (i18n).\n10. Unused CSS классы.\n\nCAVEATS:\n- Dynamic imports: require(variable) — не видят статические tools.\n- Public API libraries — не удаляй exports без bump major.\n- Feature flags: проверь в production config прежде чем удалять.\n\nВЫХОД:\n- PR удаляет X файлов / Y lines.\n- Coverage не падает.\n- Bundle size уменьшился.',
   tags:["simplify","dead-code","cleanup","refactor"],difficulty:"beginner",output:"Dead code removed",related:["sm-tech-debt","rl-bundle-deep"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"sm-tech-debt",m:"/simplify",mk:"claude",role:"Technical Debt Triage",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4B3}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Technical debt triage + roadmap.\n\nINVENTORY:\n- TODO / FIXME / HACK grep.\n- ESLint disable / # type: ignore / @ts-expect-error.\n- Long files (> 500 lines).\n- Functions > 100 lines.\n- Cyclomatic complexity > 15.\n- Deprecated dependencies.\n- Out-of-date README / docs.\n- Missing tests (coverage < 50% в critical modules).\n\nCATEGORIES:\n1. Bug risk (race conditions, memory leaks, error swallowing).\n2. Performance (N+1, sync I/O в hot path).\n3. Security (old crypto, missing CSRF, verbose logs).\n4. DX (slow CI, flaky tests, poor DI).\n5. Maintenance (dead code, unclear naming, tight coupling).\n\nSCORE:\n- Impact (1-5) × Effort (1-5) → priority.\n- Quadrant: high-impact/low-effort — do first.\n\nOUTPUT:\n- Debt backlog в issue tracker.\n- 20% sprint capacity на debt.\n- Quarterly review: debt trending down?',
   tags:["tech-debt","refactor","triage","simplify"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Debt backlog",related:["sm-dead-code","rl-strangler"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"sm-dep-graph",m:"/simplify",mk:"claude",role:"Dependency Graph Analysis",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F578}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Проанализируй dependency graph проекта.\n\nTOOLS:\n- madge (JS): graph визуализация.\n- dep-cruiser: rules + violations.\n- pydeps (Python).\n- jdeps (Java).\n- dotted (Ruby).\n\nFIND:\n1. Circular dependencies — фундаментальная проблема.\n2. "God modules": impoted > 20 раз.\n3. Too-deep nesting (> 5 levels).\n4. Layer violations: UI импортит DB напрямую.\n5. Upward dependencies: child module импортит parent.\n\nRULES (dep-cruiser config):\n- domain не импортит infrastructure.\n- utilities не импортят features.\n- no-orphans: все modules reachable.\n\nFIX:\n- Extract shared kernel (utilities, types).\n- Dependency injection вместо прямых imports.\n- Facade / adapter для внешних deps.\n- Event-driven вместо direct call.\n\nOUTPUT:\n- Graph PNG / SVG.\n- Violations list.\n- Proposed refactoring sequence.',
   tags:["dependencies","graph","architecture","simplify"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Dep analysis",related:["sm-complexity","rl-modular-monolith"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"sm-complexity",m:"/simplify",mk:"claude",role:"Complexity Reduction",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F9E9}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Reduce cyclomatic complexity.\n\nMEASURE:\n- ESLint complexity rule (threshold 10).\n- Radon (Python): radon cc -a.\n- SonarQube: cognitive complexity.\n- Cyclomatic vs Cognitive (second учитывает nesting).\n\nREDUCERS:\n1. Early return: убери else после return.\n2. Guard clauses: validate в начале, main logic плоский.\n3. Extract method: куски кода в named functions.\n4. Replace nested conditionals с polymorphism / strategy.\n5. Replace magic numbers с constants.\n6. Lookup table / map вместо switch.\n7. Boolean simplification (De Morgan).\n8. Separate concerns — один function одну задачу.\n\nТАРГЕТ:\n- Cyclomatic < 10 per function.\n- Cognitive < 15.\n- Function length < 50 lines.\n- Nesting depth < 4.\n\nPROCESS:\n- Identify top 10 complex functions.\n- Refactor one-by-one с тестами.\n- Measure до/после.',
   tags:["complexity","simplify","refactor","clean-code"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Simpler code",related:["sm-tech-debt"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"sm-naming",m:"/simplify",mk:"claude",role:"Naming Cleanup",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F3F7}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~30m-1h",
   text:'Naming / renaming cleanup pass.\n\nPRINCIPLES:\n1. Intention-revealing: getUserById не findUser(1).\n2. Consistent: create vs add vs insert — выбери один.\n3. Pronounceable: mtCntrlr → metricsController.\n4. Searchable: config_2024 > c24.\n5. No Hungarian prefixes: strName → name.\n6. Plural для collections: users, user для single.\n7. Boolean: isActive, hasPermission, canEdit.\n8. Events: past tense (userRegistered), commands: imperative (registerUser).\n9. Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE.\n10. Private (protected): _underscore / # по конвенции языка.\n\nDOMAIN:\n- Ubiquitous language: код = язык бизнеса.\n- Не смешивай синонимы (Order vs Purchase vs Transaction).\n\nTOOLS:\n- rename-refactoring IDE (VSCode F2, IntelliJ Shift+F6).\n- Типизированный refactor учитывает ссылки.\n\nLIMITATIONS:\n- Public API: не переименовывай без deprecation period.\n- DB columns: миграция + backward compat period.',
   tags:["naming","refactor","clean-code","simplify"],difficulty:"beginner",output:"Better names",related:["sm-complexity"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"cr-architecture",m:"/code-review",mk:"claude",role:"Architecture Boundary Review",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F3DB}",ac:"#ef4444",time:"~1h",
   text:'Architecture boundary review.\n\nCHECKS:\n1. Layering: UI → Application → Domain → Infrastructure. No backward imports?\n2. Module boundaries: public API only — нет импорта internals соседнего модуля?\n3. Abstractions: зависимости на интерфейсы, не на реализации?\n4. Cohesion: классы/модули делают одну вещь?\n5. Coupling: низкое coupling между модулями?\n6. Domain leakage: ORM entities не в API response?\n7. Patterns consistency: CQRS/Hex/MVC применяется единообразно?\n8. Shared kernel: общий код в /shared, не копия в каждом модуле.\n9. Cross-cutting: logging/auth/caching через decorators/middleware, не inline.\n10. Testability: core testable без DB / network / time?\n\nSMELLS:\n- Circular imports.\n- God objects.\n- Anemic domain models (вся логика в services, domain только data).\n- Feature envy (класс X больше работает с полями класса Y).\n\nВЫХОД:\n- Architectural violations с file:line.\n- Refactoring предложения + приоритет.',
   tags:["architecture","review","boundaries","clean-code"],difficulty:"advanced",output:"Arch review",related:["sm-dep-graph","rl-hexagonal"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
);

// ── Backend patterns (7) ──
add.push(
  {id:"fd-idempotency-keys",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Idempotency Keys",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F511}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Реализуй idempotency keys для POST endpoints.\n\nПРОБЛЕМА:\n- Сеть упала, клиент retry.\n- Без idempotency — duplicate resource (двойной платёж).\n\nРЕШЕНИЕ:\n- Клиент передаёт Idempotency-Key header (UUID).\n- Server: проверь key в storage. Если есть → верни cached response.\n- Если нет → обработать, сохранить (key, response) в storage.\n- TTL: 24h-7d.\n\nSTORAGE:\n- Redis: SET key value NX EX 86400.\n- Postgres: таблица (key PK, request_hash, response, created_at).\n\nCONCURRENCY:\n- Lock per key: NX atomic insert (409 Conflict если уже обрабатывается).\n- Или advisory lock в DB.\n\nREQUEST HASH:\n- Сравнивай хэш body — если другой при том же key → 422 (клиент отправил разные запросы с тем же key).\n\nSCOPE:\n- Обязательно для payment, order creation.\n- Опционально для update (обычно безопасно retry).\n- GET не нуждается (idempotent по spec).\n\nCLIENT SIDE:\n- Generate UUID per user action.\n- Retry с тем же key на network error.',
   tags:["idempotency","api","reliability","backend"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Idempotency",related:["fd-retry-backoff","fd-circuit-breaker"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-circuit-breaker",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Circuit Breaker",type:"command",icon:"\u{26A1}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~1h",
   text:'Реализуй circuit breaker.\n\nПРИНЦИП:\n- Closed: все requests проходят (нормально).\n- Open: все requests failed without attempt (защищаем downstream).\n- Half-open: пробуем несколько → закрываем если ок.\n\nTRANSITIONS:\n- Closed → Open: threshold (50% errors за 10s, или 5 consecutive fails).\n- Open → Half-open: после cooldown (30s).\n- Half-open → Closed: после N success.\n- Half-open → Open: на первом fail.\n\nLIBRARIES:\n- opossum (Node).\n- tenacity + custom (Python).\n- Resilience4j (Java).\n- Hystrix (deprecated, не используй).\n- Service mesh (Istio) — network-level.\n\nFALLBACK:\n- Cached response (stale-while-error).\n- Default / empty result.\n- Ошибка клиенту с proper code (503).\n\nMETRICS:\n- State changes logged.\n- Prometheus metric: circuit_state{name="payment-api"}.\n- Alert: open > 5 min.\n\nSCOPE:\n- Per-downstream (payment, email, push).\n- НЕ глобально.',
   tags:["circuit-breaker","resilience","fault-tolerance","backend"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"CB wrapper",related:["fd-retry-backoff","rl-bulkhead"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-retry-backoff",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Retry + Exponential Backoff",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F504}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~45m",
   text:'Реализуй retry + exponential backoff.\n\nWHEN:\n- Transient errors: network timeout, 5xx, 429.\n- НЕ: 4xx (badly-formed request).\n- НЕ: non-idempotent без idempotency key.\n\nSTRATEGY:\n- Exponential: 100ms, 200ms, 400ms, 800ms...\n- Jitter: randomize (avoid thundering herd).\n- Cap: max 30s or 5s (по случаю).\n- Budget: max 3-5 attempts total.\n\nLIBRARIES:\n- tenacity (Python): @retry decorator с политиками.\n- p-retry (JS).\n- retry-go / go-retryablehttp.\n- Resilience4j retry.\n\nCONFIG:\n```\n@retry(stop_after_attempt(5), wait_exponential(multiplier=1, min=1, max=30), retry_if_exception_type(TimeoutError))\n```\n\nJITTER:\n- equal: random(0, delay).\n- decorrelated: sleep = min(cap, random(base, sleep * 3)).\n\nMONITOR:\n- Metric: retries_total{service, reason}.\n- Log: attempt #, last error.\n- Alert: high retry rate может скрыть реальную проблему.',
   tags:["retry","backoff","resilience","jitter","backend"],difficulty:"beginner",output:"Retry logic",related:["fd-circuit-breaker","fd-idempotency-keys"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-bg-jobs",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Background Jobs",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F3ED}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Background jobs (BullMQ / RQ / Sidekiq / Celery).\n\nВЫБОР:\n- Node: BullMQ (Redis-backed).\n- Python: RQ (простой), Celery (мощный), arq.\n- Ruby: Sidekiq.\n- Go: Asynq, Machinery.\n\nPATTERNS:\n- Enqueue: веб-хендлер кладёт job в queue.\n- Worker: отдельный процесс обрабатывает.\n- Priority queues (high / normal / low).\n- Delayed jobs (scheduled).\n- Recurring (cron).\n\nREQUIREMENTS:\n- Idempotent (same job twice — один результат).\n- Small payload (ID, не весь объект).\n- Structured logs с job_id.\n- Timeout (default 30s, configurable).\n- Retry с backoff (max 3).\n- Dead-letter queue для failed jobs.\n\nSCALE:\n- Concurrent workers per queue.\n- Autoscale по queue depth.\n- Graceful shutdown: finish in-flight, не pick новые.\n\nMONITOR:\n- Queue depth per queue.\n- Job duration p95.\n- Failure rate.\n- DLQ size (alert если > 10).',
   tags:["background-jobs","queue","bullmq","celery","backend"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"BG jobs",related:["rl-queue-deadletter","fd-feature-flags"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-feature-flags",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Feature Flags",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F6A9}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Feature flags (Unleash / OpenFeature / LaunchDarkly).\n\nТИПЫ:\n- Release toggle: hide incomplete features.\n- Experiment toggle: A/B test.\n- Ops toggle: kill switch для problematic features.\n- Permission toggle: per-user / per-plan access.\n\nEVALUATION:\n- SDK queries flag service.\n- Cached locally (TTL 30s).\n- Fallback value if flag service down.\n\nCONTEXT:\n- userId, userRole, plan, country, app_version.\n- Targeting rules: if country == "KZ" → enabled.\n- Percentage rollout (стабильный hash).\n\nMANAGEMENT:\n- UI для non-devs (PM toggles flags).\n- Audit log изменений.\n- Scheduled (turn on at date).\n- Expiration reminder (flags rot).\n\nCODE:\nif (flags.isEnabled("new-checkout", {userId, plan})) { ... } else { ... }.\n\nCLEAN UP:\n- После full rollout → remove flag.\n- Dashboard: "stale flags" список.\n- Linter rule: flags старше 90 дней.\n\nSELF-HOSTED:\n- Unleash: OSS, PostgreSQL + API + UI.\n- GrowthBook: OSS, experiment-focused.',
   tags:["feature-flags","experiment","rollout","backend"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Flag system",related:["fd-bg-jobs"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"rl-queue-deadletter",m:"/ralph-loop",mk:"claude",role:"Queue + Dead Letter Queue",type:"command",icon:"\u{26B0}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'/ralph-loop "' + E + 'ЗАДАЧА: Queue + Dead Letter Queue pattern.\n\nDLQ:\n- Сообщение failed N раз → в DLQ (не теряется, но и не блокирует основную очередь).\n- Отдельный queue с тем же schema.\n- Alert: DLQ size > threshold.\n\nSETUP:\n- SQS: DLQ = отдельная queue, redrive policy (max receives 3).\n- RabbitMQ: x-dead-letter-exchange.\n- Kafka: отдельный topic для errors.\n- BullMQ / Sidekiq: встроенный DLQ.\n\nDEBUGGING:\n- Dashboard: DLQ messages с payload + error + attempts.\n- Reprocess: drain DLQ → main queue после fix.\n- Filter: по error type, time, affected user.\n\nPOISON MESSAGE:\n- Схема changed, старое сообщение не парсится.\n- Bug в consumer.\n- Missing dependency (external API gone).\n\nRETRY STRATEGY:\n- Immediate retry (transient).\n- Delayed retry (429 rate limited).\n- Exponential backoff.\n- After max retries → DLQ.\n\nTRIAGE:\n- Developer on-call checks DLQ daily.\n- Root cause → fix + backfill.' + A + '" --completion-promise "DONE"',
   tags:["queue","dlq","reliability","messaging"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"DLQ setup",related:["fd-bg-jobs","rl-kafka-setup"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"cr-backend-patterns",m:"/code-review",mk:"claude",role:"Backend Patterns Review",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F50D}",ac:"#10b981",time:"~30m",
   text:'Backend patterns code review.\n\nCHECKS:\n1. Transactions: есть ли atomic boundaries? Все запросы в транзакции где надо?\n2. N+1 queries: ORM lazy loading в циклах?\n3. Error handling: логирование + rethrow, не swallowing?\n4. Timeouts: все external calls имеют timeout?\n5. Retry: idempotent operations только?\n6. Rate limits: на dangerous endpoints?\n7. Pagination: unbounded queries?\n8. Validation: all user input?\n9. Authorization: check per endpoint (RBAC/ABAC)?\n10. Caching: headers, CDN, Redis?\n11. Observability: structured logs + metrics + traces?\n12. Secrets: не в коде / env?\n\nPATTERNS:\n- Repository: инкапсулирует DB access.\n- UoW: unit of work для транзакций.\n- Command/Query: разделение (CQRS-lite).\n- Service layer: orchestration.\n- Strategy: polymorphism вместо if/else.\n\nANTI-PATTERNS:\n- God services (>500 LoC).\n- Shotgun surgery (1 change → 20 files).\n- Feature envy.\n- Primitive obsession.\n\nВЫХОД: issues list + severity.',
   tags:["backend","review","patterns","best-practices"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Backend review",related:["cr-architecture","cr-security-deep"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
);

// ── Frontend patterns (6) ──
add.push(
  {id:"fd-state-mgmt",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"State Management Setup",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F9EE}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'State management comparison + setup.\n\nВЫБОР (2026):\n- React useState / useReducer + Context: small apps.\n- Zustand: средние, простой API.\n- Jotai: atomic, fine-grained.\n- Redux Toolkit: большие, team-heavy, DevTools.\n- Signals (Preact Signals, Solid-like): reactive.\n\nSERVER STATE (отдельно):\n- TanStack Query: cache + invalidation.\n- SWR: lighter.\n- RTK Query: если уже Redux.\n\nZUSTAND ШАБЛОН:\n```\nconst useStore = create((set) => ({\n  count: 0,\n  increment: () => set((s) => ({count: s.count + 1})),\n  reset: () => set({count: 0})\n}));\n```\n\nSLICES:\nБольшой store → разбить на slices (auth, cart, ui).\nCombine через create().\n\nDEVTOOLS:\n- Zustand: middleware devtools.\n- Redux DevTools Extension.\n\nPERSISTENCE:\n- middleware persist (localStorage / AsyncStorage).\n- Partialize: persist только часть state.\n\nSERVER ≠ CLIENT STATE:\n- Fetched data — query cache.\n- UI state — Zustand / Context.\n- НЕ смешивай.',
   tags:["state","zustand","redux","jotai","frontend"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"State setup",related:["fd-forms-ux","cr-frontend-perf"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-forms-ux",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Forms UX (Zod + RHF)",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4DD}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Forms UX с Zod + React Hook Form.\n\nSTACK:\n- React Hook Form: минимум re-renders, uncontrolled.\n- Zod: schema validation + type inference.\n- zodResolver от @hookform/resolvers.\n\nSCHEMA:\n```\nconst schema = z.object({\n  email: z.string().email(),\n  password: z.string().min(8).regex(/[A-Z]/).regex(/[0-9]/),\n  confirmPassword: z.string()\n}).refine(d => d.password === d.confirmPassword, {path: ["confirmPassword"]});\ntype Form = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n```\n\nUX:\n- Valid onBlur, не onChange (не дерзит).\n- Required + optional визуально отличаются.\n- Error messages: конкретные, не "invalid".\n- Inline errors (под полем), не в alert.\n- Submit button disabled пока invalid + dirty.\n- Loading state на async submit.\n- Server errors: setError("root", msg) или field-level.\n- Success: toast + redirect / reset form.\n\nA11Y:\n- <label htmlFor>.\n- aria-invalid, aria-describedby.\n- role="alert" для error.\n- Focus первое error поле on submit.\n\nFIELD TYPES:\n- Masked input (phone, card).\n- Autocomplete (browser, address).\n- Multi-select с search.\n- File upload с progress.',
   tags:["forms","zod","react-hook-form","ux","validation"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Form component",related:["fd-a11y-deep"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-infinite-scroll-v2",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Windowed Infinite Scroll",type:"command",icon:"\u{221E}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~1-2h",
   text:'Windowed infinite scroll с virtualization.\n\nBACKEND:\n- Cursor-based pagination (не offset — inconsistent при inserts).\n- GET /items?cursor=abc&limit=20 → {items, next_cursor}.\n- Cursor = base64(last_id + created_at).\n\nFRONTEND:\n- TanStack Query useInfiniteQuery.\n- getNextPageParam: (lastPage) => lastPage.next_cursor.\n- IntersectionObserver на sentinel в конце списка.\n- hasNextPage + isFetchingNextPage → UI.\n\nVIRTUALIZATION:\n- TanStack Virtual (headless) или react-window.\n- Только видимые items в DOM.\n- Estimated item height + dynamic measurement.\n- Window + overscan (несколько items выше/ниже viewport).\n\nUX:\n- Loading indicator внизу.\n- "End of list" message.\n- Restore scroll position при navigate back.\n- Pull-to-refresh (mobile).\n- Empty state для first page.\n- Error state + retry.\n\nPERF:\n- Prefetch next page когда 75% scroll.\n- Debounce scroll handler.\n- key={item.id} стабильный.',
   tags:["infinite-scroll","virtualization","pagination","tanstack"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Infinite list",related:["fd-virtualize-list","cr-frontend-perf"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-virtualize-list",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"List Virtualization",type:"command",icon:"\u{1F4CB}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~1h",
   text:'List virtualization (TanStack Virtual / react-window).\n\nWHEN:\n- Список > 100 items → virtualize.\n- Table > 1000 rows.\n- Grid с много cells.\n\nTANSTACK VIRTUAL:\n```\nconst virtualizer = useVirtualizer({\n  count: items.length,\n  getScrollElement: () => parentRef.current,\n  estimateSize: () => 50,\n  overscan: 5\n});\n```\n\nHEIGHT:\n- Fixed: estimateSize = fixed value.\n- Dynamic: measureElement callback.\n- Grid: horizontal + vertical virtualizers.\n\nRENDER:\n```\n<div style={{height: virtualizer.getTotalSize()}}>\n  {virtualizer.getVirtualItems().map(vi => (\n    <div key={vi.key} style={{\n      transform: `translateY(${vi.start}px)`,\n      position: "absolute", top:0, left:0\n    }}>\n      {items[vi.index]}\n    </div>\n  ))}\n</div>\n```\n\nCAVEATS:\n- Keyboard navigation: focus tracking (focused item должен быть rendered).\n- Screen reader: aria-rowcount / aria-rowindex.\n- Scroll restoration: сохранить virtualItem index, не scrollTop.\n- Dynamic height: jitter — use resize observer.',
   tags:["virtualization","tanstack-virtual","react-window","performance"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Virtual list",related:["fd-infinite-scroll-v2"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"fd-a11y-deep",m:"/feature-dev",mk:"claude",role:"Deep Accessibility",type:"command",icon:"\u{267F}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~2-3h",
   text:'Deep a11y: keyboard + screen reader.\n\nKEYBOARD:\n1. Все интерактивные элементы достижимы через Tab.\n2. Focus visible (ring) на keyboard focus, не mouse.\n3. Tab order логичный (DOM order, не CSS).\n4. Esc закрывает modals / menus.\n5. Enter / Space активируют buttons.\n6. Arrow keys в списках / menus / tabs.\n7. Home / End prodaki для списков.\n8. No tabindex > 0.\n9. Skip link "Skip to main content" в header.\n\nFOCUS TRAP:\n- Modal: focus locked внутри.\n- Return focus на trigger после close.\n\nSCREEN READER:\n- aria-label на icon-only buttons.\n- aria-labelledby для связи с heading.\n- aria-describedby для hints / errors.\n- aria-live="polite" для dynamic updates.\n- aria-live="assertive" только для critical.\n- role="alert" для errors.\n- aria-hidden="true" для декоративного.\n\nLANDMARKS:\n- <header>, <nav>, <main>, <aside>, <footer>.\n- <section aria-labelledby="heading-id">.\n\nFORMS:\n- <label> связан с input.\n- Required с aria-required.\n- Errors с aria-invalid + aria-describedby.\n\nTESTS:\n- axe-core automated.\n- Manual: screen reader (NVDA / VoiceOver / TalkBack).\n- Keyboard only пройди flow.',
   tags:["a11y","accessibility","keyboard","screen-reader","wcag"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"A11y deep",related:["fd-forms-ux"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
  {id:"cr-frontend-perf",m:"/code-review",mk:"claude",role:"Frontend Perf Review",type:"command",icon:"\u{26A1}",ac:"#0ea5e9",time:"~30m",
   text:'Frontend performance review (CWV).\n\nCORE WEB VITALS:\n- LCP < 2.5s: largest contentful paint.\n- INP < 200ms: interaction to next paint.\n- CLS < 0.1: cumulative layout shift.\n\nLCP CHECKS:\n1. Critical image: preload + priority.\n2. Fonts: font-display: swap + preload.\n3. Server response time (TTFB < 800ms).\n4. Render-blocking: inline critical CSS, defer non-critical JS.\n5. Avoid large JS в initial bundle.\n\nINP CHECKS:\n6. Long tasks > 50ms в main thread?\n7. Event handlers отправляют синхронные heavy вычисления?\n8. React: avoidUnnecessary re-renders (memo, useMemo, useCallback).\n9. Debounce input handlers.\n10. Worker для heavy parsing.\n\nCLS CHECKS:\n11. Images / videos: width + height атрибуты.\n12. Fonts: no FOUT jump (size-adjust, font-display: optional).\n13. Ads / embeds: reserved space.\n14. Dynamic content: appear без layout shift.\n15. CSS animations: transform / opacity only, не top/left.\n\nTOOLS:\n- Lighthouse (DevTools).\n- WebPageTest.\n- Chrome DevTools Performance panel.\n- Real User Monitoring (RUM): web-vitals library → send to analytics.\n\nВЫХОД: CWV score + top 5 improvements.',
   tags:["frontend","performance","cwv","lcp","cls","review"],difficulty:"intermediate",output:"Perf review",related:["rl-bundle-deep","rl-lazy-load"],prereqs:[],v:"11.0"},
);

